Rating: 3
Great recipe! Everyone in my family loves it, from my 4-year-old to my husband. I used the zest from three lemons, and 2% Greek yogurt since that's what I had on hand. Just before popping it into the oven, I squeezed out some lemon juice across the top and sprinkled a bit of demerara sugar. The results were lovely. Mine was done at 40 minutes. I think a little less oil next time would lighten it up a bit; it has a really nice crumb but was a tiny bit heavy. But still wonderfully delicious, lemony without being tart, sweet enough without being too much. Terrific.

